Bit-wise Operators : 

Binary AND &
Binary OR |
Binary XOR ^
Binary One's Complement ~
Binary Left Shift <<
Binary Right Shift >>

*Rules for and or and not are same as you have already studied as true false and 0 1s...

FORMULA FOR BINARY LEFT AND RIGHT SHIFT OPERATOR : 
Binary Left Shift << : a << b : a * 2^b; 
Binary Right Shift >> : a >> b : a/2^b;

Operations : 

Get ith bit 
Set ith bit 
Clear ith bit 
